OL,3,CRugby legend Gerald Davies left
OL,4,C'humbled and moved' by knighthood
OL,6,F"I have always believed that I should
OL,7,Fparticipate in the game.
OL,9,F"Once the game, playing-wise, was over
OL,10,FI always wanted to do something in
OL,11,Faddition to that, not just as a
OL,12,Fplayer, but as an administrator for
OL,13,FWales, the Lions, the Barbarians.
OL,15,F"I am not involved now in the earnest
OL,16,Fway that I have been right throughout
OL,17,Fmy life. It is nice and calm, and I
OL,18,Flike it that way, to look at it from a
OL,19,Fdistance.
